1
00:00:10,301 --> 00:00:13,138
THE LOVE LAB

2
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:18,143
-Ji-young.
-Oh, it's me?

3
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,229
Hyun-jin.

4
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:27,861
"Go to…"

5
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:29,821
"The space you want."

6
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,406
"Except for the starting point."

7
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:40,415
HAVE A NICE, COLD DRINK

8
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:44,002
You understand
the rules of the game, right?

9
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:46,045
Hyun-jin.

10
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:47,714
Did you just want a drink?

11
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:49,674
I'm the only one who didn't drink.

12
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:54,929
Do you understand that you get a benefit
if you complete two laps first?

13
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:55,847
Yeah.

14
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:04,105
SI-HYUN

15
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:07,984
"Pick someone you like
and ask them two questions."

16
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:10,779
I pick Hyun-jin.

17
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:17,410
I want to know the percentage
of how much you're into me

18
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:18,870
and

19
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:22,499
whether you've made your final decision.
I want to ask these two.

20
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:25,710
It's 70%.

21
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:28,463
As for the final decision,

22
00:01:28,546 --> 00:01:30,215
I haven't made up my mind yet.

23
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,595
JI-YOUNG

24
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:38,431
"Ask one question to the person you want."

25
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:42,560
I pick Si-hyun.

26
00:01:43,144 --> 00:01:45,647
Have you made up your mind
on who you'll choose

27
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:47,190
for your final decision?

28
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:50,401
At this moment…

29
00:01:58,368 --> 00:01:59,285
Yes.

30
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:00,912
I think I have.

31
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:04,541
I'm up, right?

32
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:05,542
Go ahead.

33
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:06,668
JUN-SEUNG

34
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:09,087
PICK SOMEONE YOU LIKE
AND ASK THEM TWO QUESTIONS

35
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:10,004
Two questions?

36
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,137
Was the curry good?

37
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,847
-What?
-Was the curry good?

38
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,265
Yes.

39
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:25,687
Do you want it again sometime?

40
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:28,064
Yes.

41
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:36,656
HYUN-JIN

42
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:37,824
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT

43
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:38,950
"The Room of Truth."

44
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:41,411
I pick Si-hyun.

45
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:44,455
Were you happy

46
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:47,000
to find out that I'm older than you?

47
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:47,959
Yes.

48
00:02:50,837 --> 00:02:51,880
I was happy.

49
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:57,051
I thought you'd be much younger than me.

50
00:02:58,553 --> 00:02:59,470
So I was happy.

51
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:05,894
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT
THE SELECTED PERSON CANNOT REJECT IT

52
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:07,395
I pick Hyun-jin.

53
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:13,776
If your feelings for me are at 70%,
what's the meaning of the remaining 30%?

54
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:15,862
The 30%?

55
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:21,200
The remaining 30% is…

56
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:28,416
because I thought you'd be older than me.

57
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:33,671
I think I have a lot on my mind

58
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:36,174
regarding that.

59
00:03:40,553 --> 00:03:42,931
CHARLESENTER
YOUTUBER WITH 1.04 MILLION FOLLOWERS

60
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:43,848
JUNBBANG JOGYO

61
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,516
She really wanted someone older.

62
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:47,644
She doesn't mean that, does she?

63
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:50,396
I think she means it.
She's brought it up a few times already.

64
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:53,483
No, I don't think so.

65
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,276
She doesn't want to get hurt,

66
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:58,154
so she's saving that 30%. But since she
doesn't have a good excuse for that…

67
00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:00,949
Is it an excuse she came up with
in case it doesn't work out?

68
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:05,203
But if she keeps bringing it up,
it'll keep bothering him too.

69
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:10,667
JI-YOUNG

70
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,794
"Ask them two questions."

71
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:15,922
Well, Si-hyun.

72
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:19,509
You said you'd made up your mind
about who you'll choose

73
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,261
for the final decision.

74
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,930
What is your reason
for choosing that person?

75
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:28,142
She was very direct
about her feelings for me.

76
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:33,314
One more?

77
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,736
If you met me

78
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:41,489
not in here,

79
00:04:42,323 --> 00:04:45,368
but out there…

80
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:47,495
If we met as man and woman,

81
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:50,039
do you think you'd date me?

82
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,423
If I got to know you better, maybe?

83
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:03,553
I'm up.

84
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,054
JUN-SEUNG

85
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:06,973
The Room of Truth.

86
00:05:07,056 --> 00:05:08,057
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT

87
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:09,976
This one's for Ji-young.

88
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:14,105
Did you like the convenience store
or the beach?

89
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:22,739
I liked the beach a bit more.

90
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:31,831
<i>I felt that something definitely happened</i>
<i>between the two of them.</i>

91
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:34,167
I didn't regret asking her

92
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,836
since I could find out how she's feeling.

93
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:43,801
HYUN-JIN

94
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:50,808
"Whisper 'I like you' to the person
you gave the Heart Chips to yesterday."

95
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:55,980
What if I gave them to two people?

96
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,983
-Pick one.
-Pick one?

97
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:06,282
I like you.

98
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:13,998
SI-HYUN

99
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:17,085
ASK THE WOMAN YOU LIKE
TO FEED YOU A SNACK

100
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:19,420
Feed me…

101
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:24,175
the coffee-coated peanut.

102
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:30,932
I took it as his expression
of interest in me,

103
00:06:31,015 --> 00:06:33,226
so I looked for the coffee-coated peanut,

104
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:35,228
but I didn't know what it was.

105
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,313
What is that?

106
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:40,149
This one.

107
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:42,819
Not this?

108
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:44,737
-This one?
-Just give me what you want.

109
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:45,947
That's corn.

110
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,911
So I just gave him whatever.

111
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,335
I'll tell you later
what I actually asked for.

112
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:03,798
JI-YOUNG

113
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:07,593
"Feed a snack
to someone you're interested in."

114
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,435
Which one is the coffee-coated peanut?

115
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:17,687
Isn't it this one?

116
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:19,647
Is it this?

117
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:28,156
That's the right one.

118
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:30,575
<i>There was only one hidden,</i>

119
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:32,452
<i>and Ji-young found it and gave it to me.</i>

120
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:35,037
Do you know
what makes this so entertaining?

121
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,706
He asked for coffee-coated peanuts,

122
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:38,875
but one gave me anything
as she didn't know

123
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,085
while the other went out of her way
to find it for him.

124
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,212
JUN-SEUNG

125
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,298
"Go to the space you want."

126
00:07:46,382 --> 00:07:47,216
I'm going to

127
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,218
have a nice, cold drink.

128
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,893
HYUN-JIN

129
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,478
One, two, three.

130
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:02,523
"Ask the person you like
to feed you a snack."

131
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:12,200
Which one is the coffee-coated peanut?

132
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,452
-What?
-What is the coffee-coated peanut?

133
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:18,873
There aren't any.

134
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,709
Really? Then, give me anything.

135
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,218
SI-HYUN

136
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:31,928
"Ask the person to your right,

137
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:34,972
'If I asked you right now,
would you be my girlfriend?'"

138
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,518
If I asked you right now,
would you be my girlfriend?

139
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:40,144
Yes.

140
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:43,564
<i>There was nothing to think about.</i>

141
00:08:44,148 --> 00:08:47,068
Rather than hesitating,

142
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:51,280
I thought answering him right away
would let him know how I felt.

143
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:53,074
<i>I was a bit surprised.</i>

144
00:08:53,157 --> 00:08:55,868
She was very direct and honest
about how she felt about me.

145
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,829
Seeing her speak so confidently
without caring what others thought

146
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,831
made me see her
in a completely different light.

147
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:10,508
"Go to the space you want."

148
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,638
"Say three things you liked
about the other person."

149
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:18,224
Si-hyun.

150
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,144
When we went on our date,

151
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:25,439
I liked how it made us feel
like a real couple.

152
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:32,530
I also liked that
we were able to talk about

153
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:36,325
things that we were curious about
and couldn't talk about before.

154
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:38,536
We were alike in many ways

155
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:41,205
and we had many similarities.
I liked that.

156
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:46,127
<i>While we were playing this game,</i>

157
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:50,548
I thought,
"Was Ji-young always that sure?"

158
00:09:50,631 --> 00:09:54,135
Then, I saw Jun-seung
and felt bad for him.

159
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:57,638
<i>He just kept staring at the floor.</i>

160
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:00,600
<i>I felt very bad about it</i>

161
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:04,395
because all the questions
were directed at one person.

162
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:07,023
I thought, "Why isn't anyone
talking to Jun-seung?"

163
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,483
He can be talkative too.

164
00:10:10,484 --> 00:10:11,527
I felt bad for him

165
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,279
because I could see he was deflated.

166
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:21,871
JUN-SEUNG

167
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,751
THE ROOM OF TRUTH
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT

168
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:28,961
-I pick Ji-young.
-Okay.

169
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:32,882
You said the date with Si-hyun
felt like a real couple's date.

170
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,593
If I showed you that side of me too,

171
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:37,470
would you be willing to
get to know me more?

172
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:39,513
I think

173
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:44,977
I'd have to get to know you better
and see how it goes for a long while.

174
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:52,151
It felt like Jun-seung
didn't have his guard up at all.

175
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:55,154
But he's tough even without it.

176
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:59,909
It was also amazing that he could
keep asking Ji-young questions.

177
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:04,330
I think I paid more attention
to Ji-young's answers

178
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:06,999
not because of Si-hyun,
but because of Jun-seung.

179
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:08,501
"Please,

180
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,252
don't hurt him."

181
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:14,131
HYUN-JIN

182
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,258
Oh, it should be here.

183
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:20,346
SI-HYUN

184
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:23,516
"Pick the person you like
and hold hands for five minutes."

185
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:33,567
Doesn't that seal the deal?

186
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:34,985
-Yeah, those two.
-Game over.

187
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,489
<i>It was so hard.</i>

188
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:43,702
We were exchanging questions about
how certain we were about our feelings.

189
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:47,540
<i>And I had to see it with my own eyes</i>
<i>and hear it with my ears.</i>

190
00:11:47,623 --> 00:11:48,999
<i>That whole situation</i>

191
00:11:49,625 --> 00:11:50,751
was very hard on me.

192
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:59,760
JI-YOUNG

193
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:03,347
"Ask one question to the person you want."

194
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,565
I pick Si-hyun.

195
00:12:14,316 --> 00:12:16,777
Compare me and Hyun-jin,

196
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:20,197
and tell me one thing
that you like more about me.

197
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:26,245
-Is that a fair question?
-Right?

198
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:28,789
That's a bit too much of a comparison.

199
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:31,834
She's definitely feeling
threatened by Hyun-jin.

200
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,545
She seemed wary of her
during their date too.

201
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,338
I bet this is why.

202
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:38,966
Let's say they had a similar vibe.
If they were both cat-like,

203
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:41,093
Ji-young could think
she has a good chance.

204
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,762
-But Hyun-jin's the complete opposite.
-Right.

205
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,348
She has no idea if she even has a chance.

206
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:48,601
That's why she wants to know
if anything sets her apart.

207
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:51,145
Compare me and Hyun-jin,

208
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:54,482
and tell me one thing
that you like more about me.

209
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:57,985
<i>I took it as an opportunity.</i>

210
00:12:58,486 --> 00:13:02,406
Hyun-jin played the game
more passively than I expected.

211
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,451
<i>I thought while she's</i>
<i>playing a bit passively,</i>

212
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:07,536
<i>I should be more forward.</i>

213
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,581
That way, it'd appeal to him more.

214
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:14,502
When I'm talking with Hyun-jin,

215
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:17,296
I have to think twice

216
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:19,381
before I speak with her.

217
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:21,550
But when I'm talking to you, Ji-young,

218
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:22,551
I'm

219
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:25,971
more at ease.

220
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:30,392
JUN-SEUNG

221
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:34,980
"Ask the person to your right,

222
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:38,984
'If I asked you right now,
would you be my girlfriend?'"

223
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:41,028
Say yes to this.

224
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:42,154
Say yes, Hyun-jin.

225
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:44,532
Why not? It's Seo In-guk.
Why couldn't she date him?

226
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:46,992
His voice is like Seo In-guk's,
and he looks like him too.

227
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:50,496
Hyun-jin, if I asked you out right now,
would you be my girlfriend?

228
00:13:56,043 --> 00:13:57,586
I can't say yes…

229
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:02,508
but it may change the way I look at you.

230
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:07,304
<i>It wasn't just us</i>

231
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:09,890
that had a good time
during those six hours?

232
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:12,226
<i>I didn't expect Hyun-jin</i>
<i>to give such an answer.</i>

233
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:15,854
I thought she'd make it clear
by saying no,

234
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:17,773
but seeing that,

235
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:20,693
I thought she was starting to waver.

236
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:26,448
That made me more determined
to stay committed and push through.

237
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:29,743
It may not be my place to say this,

238
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:31,954
but I was also hoping

239
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:36,250
that Ji-young would notice
Jun-seung a bit more.

240
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,585
He's an attractive person,

241
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:41,046
but it seems like she can't see his charm.

242
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:43,465
I do feel sorry for Jun-seung.

243
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,759
-But he <i>is</i> admirable.
-He is.

244
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:48,721
Hyun-jin found
Jun-seung's looks attractive enough

245
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:50,514
-to choose him as her ideal type, right?
-Right.

246
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:52,558
If Jun-seung hadn't
totally shut off Hyun-jin--

247
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,143
She probably still feels something.

248
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:56,020
Yeah, Hyun-jin gave
Jun-seung a Heart Chip.

249
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:57,021
You're right.

250
00:14:57,104 --> 00:14:58,439
Also, this is how women are.

251
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:01,150
She may just think of him as a friend,

252
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,693
but she wouldn't say something
she doesn't mean.

253
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:04,445
She said she'd think about it, right?

254
00:15:04,528 --> 00:15:05,988
She could really mean that.

255
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:06,906
You're right.

256
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:13,537
HYUN-JIN

257
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:16,916
"Pick someone you like
and ask them two questions."

258
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:19,835
-Si-hyun.
-Yeah?

259
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:23,464
How would you have felt
if I were younger than you?

260
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:28,093
I'd still have wanted
to get to know you.

261
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:32,056
We got to know each other in this place

262
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:33,974
without any background information, right?

263
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:37,353
Without knowing anything
about your background,

264
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,356
I got curious about you
and I developed feelings for you,

265
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:43,692
so even if you were younger than me,
I would've felt the same.

266
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:47,613
SI-HYUN

267
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,740
Three. One, two, three.

268
00:15:49,823 --> 00:15:50,866
"The Room of Truth."

269
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:54,119
I pick Hyun-jin.

270
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:57,623
What's the main reason

271
00:15:57,706 --> 00:16:00,834
that's keeping you
from making the final decision?

272
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:05,881
For me,

273
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:11,637
I realized my ideal type
was more about their personality

274
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,348
than the appearance.

275
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:17,101
But there was another factor

276
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:21,397
that mattered just as much.

277
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,273
Stop talking about the age. Stop.

278
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,566
What is that factor?

279
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,026
Don't say it.

280
00:16:26,110 --> 00:16:27,736
It's…

281
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,324
the age.

282
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:36,829
Isn't age just an excuse?

283
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:39,415
If Si-hyun doesn't choose her,

284
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:42,084
she can say that age
was an issue for her too.

285
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:44,628
-That's right.
-Does she really want that? For real?

286
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:47,423
This is unbelievable.
This streams on Netflix, right?

287
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:49,049
Non-Korean viewers won't get her.

288
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,634
They really won't get it.

289
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:51,760
I'm serious.

290
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:55,472
I think they should explain
that this is part of Korean culture.

291
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:57,516
It's Korean culture!

292
00:16:57,599 --> 00:17:00,978
Non-Korean viewers might think
that they are like ten years apart.

293
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:05,232
JI-YOUNG

294
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:08,152
THE ROOM OF TRUTH
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT

295
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:10,571
I pick Hyun-jin.

296
00:17:10,654 --> 00:17:11,488
Okay.

297
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:17,286
Even if you like everything about a guy,

298
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:20,456
would you really not date him

299
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,791
if there's an age issue?

300
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:28,505
<i>It felt like she's really conflicted</i>
<i>about this age issue.</i>

301
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:33,927
So I asked her that question on purpose
to bring out the subject about the age.

302
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,637
It was directed at Si-hyun.

303
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,016
Well,

304
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,894
I was thinking a lot about that
since early this morning.

305
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,442
It won't be easy.

306
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:49,943
-What?
-What?

307
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:55,240
<i>She said it would be hard</i>
<i>if the guy's younger than her.</i>

308
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:58,494
She made that point clear,
so I felt relieved.

309
00:17:58,577 --> 00:18:02,164
Her answer was exactly
the kind of answer I was fishing for.

310
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:04,458
It won't be easy.

311
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:09,671
<i>If she had said that</i>
<i>while she was with me alone,</i>

312
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:13,383
<i>I would have been aware of it,</i>
<i>but I had no clue</i>

313
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:17,012
<i>and I heard about her thoughts on the age</i>
<i>for the first time there.</i>

314
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:18,388
So I thought, "I see."

315
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:22,351
<i>"She may not choose me in the end."</i>

316
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:26,480
She said she couldn't date a younger guy,

317
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:28,732
<i>but then, she showed her interest in me.</i>

318
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:31,485
I couldn't tell what she was thinking.

319
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:34,988
They didn't reveal their ages now.
They did it yesterday, right?

320
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:36,865
-Right.
-But she still liked him.

321
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:40,035
Yeah, she gave him 88 Heart Chips
and took him to the Attic House.

322
00:18:44,289 --> 00:18:45,707
HYUN-JIN

323
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,168
THE ROOM OF TRUTH
ASK ONE QUESTION TO THE PERSON YOU WANT

324
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,255
I pick Si-hyun.

325
00:18:52,339 --> 00:18:55,175
If we were given one extra day,

326
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:58,887
who would you like to take on a date?

327
00:19:00,013 --> 00:19:00,848
I'd pick you.

328
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,568
It's over.

329
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,070
Come on.

330
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,822
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

331
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:19,533
<i>Love Marble has ended.</i>

332
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:25,080
<i>They want us to check the mailbox.</i>

333
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,457
"The Fireplace House has opened."

334
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:34,006
"You can enjoy a private date here
with the person of your choice."

335
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:38,468
"The winner of Love Marble should
choose someone and head there now."

336
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:48,312
I'll go with Ji-young.

337
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:52,566
Does this even make sense?

338
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:56,778
He may have done that

339
00:19:56,862 --> 00:20:00,199
because Hyun-jin said it'd be hard
for her to get over the age issue.

340
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:02,201
But then he said
he'd take her out on a date.

341
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:04,578
I'll go with Ji-young.

342
00:20:06,788 --> 00:20:08,540
<i>I thought he'd choose me.</i>

343
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,335
But he chose Ji-young,

344
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:13,545
so I figured things went to pot.

345
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,047
It's a shame.

346
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:17,925
I'll go with Ji-young.

347
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:20,928
<i>When he chose me,</i>

348
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:22,763
I wasn't all that happy.

349
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:26,808
I thought it meant he made up his mind
and was going to tell me his decision.

350
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:29,478
It's cold.

351
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,361
-Let's go back inside.
-Okay.

352
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:40,822
-Let's get going, Hyun-jin.
-Let's go.

353
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:51,041
A lot on your mind, huh?

354
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:53,085
-Did you have a lot on your mind?
-Yeah.

355
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:54,169
No, I mean you.

356
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,587
-What?
-Did you expect that?

357
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:56,505
About what?

358
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,675
Did you expect Si-hyun to choose Ji-young?

359
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:01,718
-Shall we talk when we get inside?
-Okay.

360
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:06,765
SI-HYUN AND JI-YOUNG
HEAD TO THE FIREPLACE HOUSE

361
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:07,933
Oh, it's over there.

362
00:21:08,016 --> 00:21:09,893
ISOLATED HOUSE
ATTIC HOUSE

363
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:11,478
FIREPLACE HOUSE

364
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:15,607
TONIGHT, THIS PLACE HAS OPENED
FOR THE TWO OF THEM TO TALK

365
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:16,942
Wow.

366
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:18,944
Wow, what's this?

367
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:31,164
This place is so fun.

368
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:33,000
It's really fun.

369
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,835
-Shall we sit by the fire? It's cold.
-Yeah.

370
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:38,839
How was it?

371
00:21:38,922 --> 00:21:40,757
What kind of mindset did you play

372
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:43,302
-Love Marble with?
-My mindset?

373
00:21:43,385 --> 00:21:44,761
-Yeah.
-What about you?

374
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:47,556
Me?

375
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,727
Get me some soju, please!

376
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,187
You're craving alcohol, aren't you?

377
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:58,358
It must've been tough.

378
00:21:58,442 --> 00:22:01,069
I felt so bad
the whole time I was watching you.

379
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:02,029
Likewise.

380
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:06,783
-You have a lot on your mind, don't you?
-On my mind?

381
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,077
I wonder if contemplating
is even worthwhile.

382
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:10,037
I don't know.

383
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:12,664
-I just…
-Do you regret it?

384
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:16,084
Regretting… I did regret it.

385
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,210
Yeah?

386
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:20,005
But I wondered if I should even regret it.

387
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:24,343
I was so surprised.

388
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:29,598
-Why?
-The Ji-young that I saw on our date

389
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:33,810
was a totally different person
from the person I saw

390
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:36,938
playing Love Marble.

391
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:39,733
<i>After playing Love Marble,</i>

392
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:42,778
my perception of Ji-young
has changed a lot.

393
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:47,074
I came to understand
what kind of thoughts she has about me

394
00:22:47,157 --> 00:22:50,160
and how big her feelings for me are.

395
00:22:50,243 --> 00:22:53,497
I don't know if you remember,
but I said I like someone

396
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,665
-who has a backbone.
-Yeah, I remember.

397
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:59,961
I don't think one person should
always be compromising

398
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:02,756
-in a relationship.
-Yeah.

399
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:05,967
But you said you can do that.

400
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:08,512
You said you can give everything up.

401
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:09,763
That was an issue for me.

402
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:13,016
That's how it was
in my previous relationships,

403
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,560
but I realized that
I shouldn't be like that anymore.

404
00:23:15,644 --> 00:23:18,814
<i>Because I liked them more,</i>
<i>I was the one who always compromised.</i>

405
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:19,898
Because I liked the guy,

406
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:21,316
everything was okay.

407
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:24,736
Even if they did something wrong,
it was all forgiven. That's how it was.

408
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:28,740
But after I got to talk
about relationships with them here,

409
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:31,493
and after hearing that Si-hyun

410
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:34,412
likes someone who has a backbone,

411
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:37,707
I realized that I shouldn't be like
how I was in my previous relationships.

412
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:40,627
You seemed so different
when we were playing the game,

413
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:43,463
and I liked that side of you.

414
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:49,970
I just didn't want to regret anything.

415
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:51,888
When we went on our date,

416
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,473
we really talked a lot, didn't we?

417
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:58,353
<i>It felt so natural,</i>
<i>like we were a real couple,</i>

418
00:23:58,436 --> 00:24:00,772
<i>so I started wondering</i>

419
00:24:00,856 --> 00:24:03,692
<i>what it would be like</i>
<i>if we actually became a real couple.</i>

420
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:08,113
I've always wanted to get closer to you,

421
00:24:08,196 --> 00:24:11,074
but I was wary of the others.

422
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:12,742
-That's how it was.
-Yeah.

423
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:17,664
You wrote that you liked women
who are refined and affectionate.

424
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:20,292
I don't think that's me.
It's probably Hyun-jin.

425
00:24:20,375 --> 00:24:21,459
Really?

426
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:24,629
<i>I was worried that</i>
<i>he wouldn't be attracted to me.</i>

427
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,298
I always had that concern,

428
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:30,218
so I kept thinking, "I hope he likes me,"

429
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:31,970
rather than approaching him first.

430
00:24:32,053 --> 00:24:34,723
This is how I've always felt.

431
00:24:34,806 --> 00:24:38,768
I wanted to go out with you
and hoped things would develop.

432
00:24:38,852 --> 00:24:39,686
That's how I felt.

433
00:24:39,769 --> 00:24:44,065
But I've been suppressing my feelings
and keeping them to myself.

434
00:24:47,694 --> 00:24:51,072
But I think you helped me muster up…

435
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:54,826
courage.

436
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,704
You helped me build that courage.

437
00:24:57,787 --> 00:25:00,248
If we don't chat here,
we can't have a birthday party together.

438
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:03,460
I'm not good at things like that.

439
00:25:03,543 --> 00:25:06,546
You couldn't do it out there,
but you can do it here.

440
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:08,840
I put everything out there

441
00:25:09,716 --> 00:25:11,927
one last time.

442
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:14,179
I have no regrets.

443
00:25:15,055 --> 00:25:16,097
I'm glad I did it.

444
00:25:16,598 --> 00:25:18,767
-It was a good date then.
-Yeah.

445
00:25:19,559 --> 00:25:21,603
<i>Si-hyun and I kept talking about this.</i>

446
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:23,647
The final decision isn't

447
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:26,650
about how we feel right now,

448
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:28,818
but it's about what we'll do out there.

449
00:25:28,902 --> 00:25:31,780
Let's say we chose each other in the end.

450
00:25:31,863 --> 00:25:34,324
Could we make this work outside of here?

451
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:36,034
I think it's totally possible,

452
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:39,371
but I'm not sure it's because
of this unique setting or…

453
00:25:39,454 --> 00:25:41,122
We may face

454
00:25:41,706 --> 00:25:42,999
-real-life issues.
-Yeah.

455
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:44,709
So why bother choosing then?

456
00:25:44,793 --> 00:25:46,086
If you're not sure…

457
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:51,633
So I thought about that a lot
and the age issue kept bothering me.

458
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:55,595
I wondered if this would work.

459
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:58,473
<i>I kept thinking about it</i>
<i>this morning after I woke up.</i>

460
00:25:58,556 --> 00:26:00,475
<i>I just kept thinking, "What do I do?"</i>

461
00:26:01,017 --> 00:26:04,271
I've never dated someone younger than me

462
00:26:04,354 --> 00:26:05,814
and never liked one either.

463
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:07,607
Even my friends are mostly
not younger than me.

464
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:10,860
I'm comfortable around older people.
I like being with them,

465
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:14,072
and I like being
the youngest one in the group.

466
00:26:14,155 --> 00:26:16,449
I think I have
a certain fantasy of men older than me.

467
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:18,243
When you guys went there,

468
00:26:18,326 --> 00:26:19,744
I had so much fun.

469
00:26:19,828 --> 00:26:22,497
-With Si-hyun?
-I had so much fun chatting with Si-hyun.

470
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:24,332
I don't want to succeed,

471
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:27,919
but I'm trying to enjoy working hard.

472
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:28,837
Wow.

473
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:31,256
You'd have to do what you love
to enjoy working hard.

474
00:26:31,339 --> 00:26:32,590
I am doing that.

475
00:26:32,674 --> 00:26:34,092
I'm the kind of person

476
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:36,511
who gives it all to the life he chose,

477
00:26:36,594 --> 00:26:37,929
and I am doing exactly that.

478
00:26:38,596 --> 00:26:39,556
That's awesome.

479
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,850
This is fun.

480
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:42,767
I'm glad.

481
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:44,728
Because you're here.

482
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:48,023
<i>I didn't expect it from him,</i>

483
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:51,318
<i>but we could actually</i>
<i>carry on a good conversation like this.</i>

484
00:26:51,401 --> 00:26:52,944
I'm younger.

485
00:26:53,028 --> 00:26:54,237
I really am younger.

486
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:57,157
-Is that what you want?
-I really am younger.

487
00:26:57,782 --> 00:27:02,078
<i>I kept wondering if he was older than me</i>
<i>while we were talking.</i>

488
00:27:02,162 --> 00:27:05,332
I was very curious about him.

489
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:07,709
The age must matter a lot to you.

490
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:10,253
It makes me feel a certain way about them.

491
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:13,089
-"Right, he's younger."
-Yeah.

492
00:27:13,173 --> 00:27:15,842
But apart from that,

493
00:27:15,925 --> 00:27:17,052
I think my feelings

494
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,679
were stronger than my doubts.

495
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:21,890
If I end up choosing Si-hyun,

496
00:27:21,973 --> 00:27:23,933
it wouldn't be
because I'm "okay" with younger men,

497
00:27:25,352 --> 00:27:28,480
but it would be <i>because</i> it's him.

498
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:31,399
So when he comes back…

499
00:27:31,483 --> 00:27:32,901
You're going to tell him?

500
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:34,652
Wouldn't we have some time?

501
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:37,447
I could explain him where I stand.

502
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:39,574
The reason why

503
00:27:40,367 --> 00:27:43,244
I put so many Heart Chips yesterday
despite knowing his age

504
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:45,914
and what I am concerned about now.

505
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:48,375
I wanted to share that with him.

506
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:52,337
When you said you'd be
my girlfriend if I asked you,

507
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:56,591
what thoughts were behind that answer?

508
00:27:57,175 --> 00:27:58,551
-What thoughts?
-Yeah.

509
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:01,971
I was just thinking
about how I felt about you.

510
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:03,431
That was it.

511
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:07,477
Let's say we started dating.
What if you don't like me?

512
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,479
I might be different
from how I've been here.

513
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:14,442
You're being genuine on this show,

514
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:16,403
so I don't think
you'd be hugely different.

515
00:28:17,779 --> 00:28:19,197
I don't think you'll be different.

516
00:28:21,199 --> 00:28:22,492
You're just you.

517
00:28:22,575 --> 00:28:24,744
-Yeah, but here, I am…
-You're you.

518
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:28,164
This is such a fascinating place.

519
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:35,422
It was tough.

520
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:40,552
<i>Around the time</i>
<i>we were wrapping up our date,</i>

521
00:28:40,635 --> 00:28:43,972
I asked you to tell me
when your mind is made up,

522
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:46,683
no matter what the decision is.

523
00:28:49,185 --> 00:28:50,061
-Yeah.
-So

524
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:51,980
the reason why you brought me here…

525
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:56,943
Am I right? Is that why?

526
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:59,404
Why did you bring me here?

527
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:03,658
After our date
and before we played Love Marble,

528
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:05,285
I kept thinking about Hyun-jin.

529
00:29:05,368 --> 00:29:06,202
When

530
00:29:06,911 --> 00:29:08,538
-we came back,
-Yeah.

531
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:10,665
I was happy to see her.

532
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:11,583
Right.

533
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:16,921
-You're here.
-Hi.

534
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:19,466
The curry smell is super strong.

535
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:21,384
-So nice and smooth, right?
-Yeah.

536
00:29:22,010 --> 00:29:24,846
<i>I was happy to see her,</i>
<i>but when I tried to make a move,</i>

537
00:29:24,929 --> 00:29:27,557
<i>it kept getting awkward.</i>

538
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:30,602
I kept walking on eggshells around her.

539
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:34,230
Even after the game,

540
00:29:34,314 --> 00:29:36,149
I think you are…

541
00:29:38,651 --> 00:29:40,862
still leaning more toward Hyun-jin.

542
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:44,407
Is that right?

543
00:29:49,621 --> 00:29:50,622
It's 70%.

544
00:29:53,082 --> 00:29:54,959
Yeah, Hyun-jin was 70%.

545
00:29:56,669 --> 00:29:58,213
But she said the age was a barrier.

546
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:02,008
She had never told me that the age
was an issue before.

547
00:30:02,091 --> 00:30:04,302
But it happened all of a sudden
after you and I got back.

548
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:06,513
-This is what I think.
-Yeah?

549
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:09,682
During the game, we said

550
00:30:09,766 --> 00:30:13,353
that we were so happy and we had
so much fun on our date.

551
00:30:13,436 --> 00:30:16,147
I think that's why she said that.

552
00:30:18,483 --> 00:30:20,276
But I wouldn't know for sure.

553
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,278
When she said her feelings
for me were at 70%,

554
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:24,239
I was going to choose Hyun-jin.

555
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:26,491
That is what I thought.

556
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:31,412
After that, the mood changed completely
during that one hour.

557
00:30:32,539 --> 00:30:33,623
It became so hard for me.

558
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,335
I won't know until the end.

559
00:30:38,419 --> 00:30:39,379
Okay.

560
00:30:42,131 --> 00:30:44,467
But anyway…

561
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:51,975
<i>While I was watching</i>
<i>how the game was going,</i>

562
00:30:52,058 --> 00:30:57,230
it looked like things might
work out for those two,

563
00:30:57,313 --> 00:31:00,191
so I felt like I should
hurry up and make up my mind.

564
00:31:00,275 --> 00:31:02,068
At the <i>hoe</i> restaurant,

565
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:04,320
when Si-hyun and I

566
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:08,199
fed each other <i>hoe</i> lettuce wraps.

567
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:12,620
<i>I felt like if I gave a vague answer,</i>

568
00:31:12,704 --> 00:31:15,123
<i>I could ruin everything.</i>

569
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:19,002
I was thinking a lot about that
since early this morning.

570
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:25,925
<i>So I said that I gave it some thought</i>
<i>and it wouldn't be easy for me,</i>

571
00:31:26,009 --> 00:31:27,135
<i>but I kind of</i>

572
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:29,012
regret saying that.

573
00:31:30,638 --> 00:31:32,849
-You wish you didn't sound so sure?
-Yeah.

574
00:31:33,433 --> 00:31:36,269
That would have been better.

575
00:31:36,352 --> 00:31:37,353
Yeah.

576
00:31:37,437 --> 00:31:41,357
I still think highly of Hyun-jin
because she knows what she did.

577
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:43,234
-Yeah, and she owned up to it.
-Yeah.

578
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:44,777
She knows it was her pride.

579
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:46,362
You know,

580
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:48,072
when I heard those two talking,

581
00:31:48,156 --> 00:31:50,700
I realized that they had a very good time.

582
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:52,619
And

583
00:31:52,702 --> 00:31:54,996
I could see that on your face too.

584
00:31:55,079 --> 00:31:56,915
You had that "Oh, no" look.

585
00:31:59,876 --> 00:32:00,793
You're right.

586
00:32:02,587 --> 00:32:03,463
That's how it was.

587
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:07,884
-Let's clink our glasses.
-Feeling down, right? I'll drink too.

588
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:16,517
You look like you're about to cry.

589
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:24,317
I learned so many things
while we were playing the game,

590
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:25,735
so Si-hyun felt different to me.

591
00:32:25,818 --> 00:32:28,571
Me too. Ji-young and Si-hyun
both felt different to me.

592
00:32:28,655 --> 00:32:31,115
I thought, "What is this feeling?"

593
00:32:31,199 --> 00:32:33,910
"I don't think it's jealousy."

594
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:37,121
So are your feelings for Hyun-jin

595
00:32:37,872 --> 00:32:39,791
still at 70%?

596
00:32:40,375 --> 00:32:42,710
My feelings for you have grown…

597
00:32:45,129 --> 00:32:47,966
but I didn't get a chance
to chat with her after the game.

598
00:32:48,549 --> 00:32:50,718
I want to know
what made her think that way.

599
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,428
-You mean, Hyun-jin?
-Yeah.

600
00:32:52,512 --> 00:32:53,554
I have to know.

601
00:32:55,306 --> 00:32:59,477
<i>I do think that Si-hyun has</i>
<i>some feelings for me.</i>

602
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:02,730
But I think he'll go with Hyun-jin
in the end anyway.

603
00:33:02,814 --> 00:33:04,983
It can't possibly be me.

604
00:33:05,066 --> 00:33:11,114
Even though Si-hyun went
on a six-hour date with me,

605
00:33:11,197 --> 00:33:12,573
I feel like…

606
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:17,036
it was too short.

607
00:33:18,329 --> 00:33:20,790
If he was leaning towards me,

608
00:33:20,873 --> 00:33:23,459
I think he would've made it clear to me.

609
00:33:23,543 --> 00:33:27,422
I actually felt like the Si-hyun
I was with at the Fireplace House

610
00:33:27,505 --> 00:33:29,257
didn't know his own mind.

611
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:32,927
I clearly expressed
how I felt during the game,

612
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:36,472
but all Si-hyun said to me
was that he was surprised

613
00:33:36,556 --> 00:33:38,683
and that he liked that side of me,

614
00:33:38,766 --> 00:33:40,226
so I really don't know where he stands.

615
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:42,979
You know,

616
00:33:43,062 --> 00:33:46,065
I feel like a wavering reed
in a field of reeds.

617
00:33:46,566 --> 00:33:48,776
-You're really conflicted.
-Yeah.

618
00:33:50,570 --> 00:33:52,363
I'm going to follow my heart.

619
00:33:55,575 --> 00:33:58,536
How is he able to
acknowledge his own flaw like that?

620
00:33:58,619 --> 00:34:01,956
Usually, people would hide
the fact that they're wavering.

621
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,207
He's very confident.

622
00:34:03,291 --> 00:34:06,085
"I like women who know their own minds,
but I'm a wavering reed." What?

623
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:07,545
<i>How should I put this?</i>

624
00:34:07,628 --> 00:34:10,965
<i>I wonder if it's okay</i>
<i>for me to even feel disappointed.</i>

625
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:12,383
As for me…

626
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:16,929
I know that I like Si-hyun,

627
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:20,808
but I wonder whether we can
actually be in a relationship.

628
00:34:20,892 --> 00:34:21,976
But for Si-hyun,

629
00:34:22,685 --> 00:34:26,773
he hasn't even decided
between me and her.

630
00:34:27,398 --> 00:34:29,442
Well, I'd like to talk to him
one more time.

631
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:33,905
I'm wondering if I should
even make my final decision.

632
00:34:33,988 --> 00:34:34,989
You should.

633
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:36,866
-Hey.
-Yeah?

634
00:34:37,658 --> 00:34:39,285
I can clearly see how she feels.

635
00:34:39,368 --> 00:34:40,620
What about how you feel?

636
00:34:40,703 --> 00:34:42,538
Yeah, I still have feelings.

637
00:34:43,122 --> 00:34:44,665
I just feel a bit stumped.

638
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,378
"You should go for it.
That would be cool."

639
00:34:49,462 --> 00:34:50,671
After I said that, I thought,

640
00:34:51,464 --> 00:34:52,465
"Yeah,

641
00:34:53,257 --> 00:34:54,967
how I feel is the most important."

642
00:34:55,051 --> 00:34:56,552
Yes, that's what matters.

643
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,848
I suppose I <i>will</i> make a final decision.

644
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:03,643
-You got something.
-Is it me?

645
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:07,438
Come on. What's this?

646
00:35:07,522 --> 00:35:10,233
WHO WILL YOU EXPRESS YOUR FEELINGS TO?
THE LAST HEART CHIP VOTE STARTS NOW

647
00:35:10,316 --> 00:35:13,528
WHO WILL YOU EXPRESS YOUR FEELINGS TO?
THE LAST HEART CHIP VOTE STARTS NOW

648
00:35:13,611 --> 00:35:17,365
YOU CAN ONLY VOTE FOR ONE PERSON TODAY

649
00:35:17,448 --> 00:35:21,786
IF YOU USE UP ALL 200 OF YOUR HEART CHIPS,
YOU MUST TELL THEM HOW YOU FEEL TOMORROW

650
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:27,500
I'm sorry.

651
00:35:27,583 --> 00:35:29,001
-About what?
-I can't give you any.

652
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:30,962
-I can't vote for you.
-I should've given you

653
00:35:31,045 --> 00:35:32,088
-Come on!
-at least one.

654
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:34,507
-I should've given you one.
-You should have.

655
00:35:34,590 --> 00:35:37,468
<i>The Heart Chip voting area</i>
<i>has opened for the last night.</i>

656
00:35:38,052 --> 00:35:39,762
<i>We hope you're able to bring</i>

657
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:42,431
<i>all the sincere and honest</i>
<i>conversations you've had here</i>

658
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:44,559
<i>to a good close.</i>

659
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:50,189
<i>I haven't heard a clear answer</i>
<i>as to whether he'll choose me or not.</i>

660
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:52,400
So I really don't know where he stands.

661
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:55,945
<i>I keep going back and forth.</i>

662
00:35:56,028 --> 00:35:57,989
<i>I am a bit torn.</i>

663
00:35:58,072 --> 00:35:59,907
-See you.
-Okay.

664
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:01,367
Don't you vote for me.

665
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:02,410
I won't.

666
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:15,089
<i>I just did what I could,</i>

667
00:36:15,173 --> 00:36:16,132
<i>and I have no regrets.</i>

668
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:23,681
<i>But I wondered if she'd date me</i>
<i>even after getting to know me for a while.</i>

669
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:32,565
WEE JUN-SEUNG
ENTERS THE VOTING AREA

670
00:36:33,608 --> 00:36:37,528
99 HEART CHIPS LEFT

671
00:36:45,703 --> 00:36:49,624
It felt wrong to me
to just stop showing interest

672
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:53,169
all of a sudden.

673
00:36:53,252 --> 00:36:54,837
It would be weird.

674
00:36:56,088 --> 00:37:00,051
It'd be kind of embarrassing too,
wouldn't it?

675
00:37:08,517 --> 00:37:11,437
WEE JUN-SEUNG COMPLETED VOTING
99 HEART CHIPS TO JI-YOUNG

676
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:26,118
<i>"Let's go on a date when we leave here."</i>

677
00:37:28,829 --> 00:37:29,872
<i>That's all I wrote.</i>

678
00:37:36,128 --> 00:37:39,715
GO ON A ROMANTIC DATE WITH ME TOO!
LET'S SEE HOW IT GOES OVER TIME!

679
00:37:46,389 --> 00:37:48,933
This is what makes Jun-seung so cool.

680
00:37:49,016 --> 00:37:50,434
People who are direct like that

681
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:53,104
aren't typically considerate
of the other person.

682
00:37:53,187 --> 00:37:55,940
But he's considerate while being direct.
That's so admirable of him.

683
00:37:56,023 --> 00:37:58,526
He's not putting too much pressure
on the other person.

684
00:37:58,609 --> 00:37:59,860
Kudos to you, Jun-seung.

685
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:01,612
-He's very thoughtful.
-Yeah.

686
00:38:05,408 --> 00:38:06,450
I went all in.

687
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:07,493
Good job.

688
00:38:08,494 --> 00:38:10,663
I really had to think hard
about what to write.

689
00:38:10,746 --> 00:38:12,331
-Guess what I wrote.
-I don't know.

690
00:38:12,415 --> 00:38:14,041
-You got a message.
-Is it mine?

691
00:38:15,459 --> 00:38:16,919
-I'll be back.
-Okay.

692
00:38:17,003 --> 00:38:18,713
HYUN-JIN, GO TO THE VOTING AREA

693
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:20,423
-Let's talk when you get back.
-Okay.

694
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:32,935
LAH HYUN-JIN
ENTERS THE VOTING AREA

695
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:39,108
108 HEART CHIPS LEFT

696
00:38:39,191 --> 00:38:41,360
<i>If I used up all of my 200 Heart Chips</i>…

697
00:38:43,779 --> 00:38:45,323
it would mean

698
00:38:45,406 --> 00:38:48,826
that I'd have to make up my mind
about the final decision.

699
00:38:48,909 --> 00:38:50,453
SHE MUST MAKE UP HER MIND

700
00:38:50,536 --> 00:38:52,788
<i>That's why I was very torn.</i>

701
00:39:00,546 --> 00:39:04,342
SHE WRITES THE MESSAGE FIRST

702
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:09,680
I WAS WAITING FOR YOU

703
00:39:13,392 --> 00:39:14,643
She always has a hidden ace.

704
00:39:14,727 --> 00:39:15,936
All she needs is one sentence.

705
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:17,563
"I was waiting for you." So cool.

706
00:39:17,646 --> 00:39:18,481
"During

707
00:39:19,398 --> 00:39:20,232
my time here,

708
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:22,151
I liked you

709
00:39:23,652 --> 00:39:25,529
and I waited for you all day today too."

710
00:39:27,239 --> 00:39:28,574
<i>I just wanted</i>

711
00:39:29,742 --> 00:39:30,785
<i>to tell him that.</i>

712
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:47,259
LAH HYUN-JIN COMPLETED VOTING
HOW MANY HEART CHIPS TO SI-HYUN?

713
00:40:00,106 --> 00:40:02,149
JI-YOUNG, GO TO THE VOTING AREA

714
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:03,776
-It's cold.
-Take the blanket.

715
00:40:03,859 --> 00:40:04,693
Okay.

716
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:10,908
<i>I could tell that</i>
<i>he had a lot on his mind.</i>

717
00:40:10,991 --> 00:40:14,537
<i>He seemed to be having a hard time,</i>
<i>and he looked troubled too.</i>

718
00:40:14,620 --> 00:40:16,664
BYEON JI-YOUNG
ENTERS THE VOTING AREA

719
00:40:17,331 --> 00:40:19,375
160 HEART CHIPS LEFT

720
00:40:19,959 --> 00:40:20,876
Gosh.

721
00:40:22,795 --> 00:40:24,505
<i>The thing is, even though</i>

722
00:40:25,089 --> 00:40:28,717
<i>we went on a really fun date</i>…

723
00:40:30,052 --> 00:40:30,970
What should I do?

724
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:36,809
It felt like his mind was already made up.

725
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:41,730
That thought weighed on me.

726
00:40:41,814 --> 00:40:44,692
She keeps telling herself this
because she doesn't want to

727
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:46,527
-be disappointed at the end.
-Right.

728
00:40:47,486 --> 00:40:48,779
It breaks my heart to watch her.

729
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:50,698
Today was their first date, right?

730
00:40:50,781 --> 00:40:52,533
She was just curious about him until then.

731
00:40:52,616 --> 00:40:55,995
Her feelings grew so much in just one day?

732
00:40:56,078 --> 00:40:58,080
Ji-young has liked Si-hyun all along.

733
00:40:58,164 --> 00:41:00,040
He's her once-in-a-millennium ideal type.

734
00:41:06,088 --> 00:41:07,256
Wait.

735
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:29,695
<i>"Let's escape</i>

736
00:41:30,821 --> 00:41:32,239
<i>this isolation together."</i>

737
00:42:04,230 --> 00:42:07,399
BYEON JI-YOUNG COMPLETED VOTING
160 HEART CHIPS TO SI-HYUN

738
00:42:07,483 --> 00:42:10,778
He told me that he's interested in me.

739
00:42:10,861 --> 00:42:14,198
I went all in after hearing that.

740
00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:16,742
Because that much seemed clear.

741
00:42:16,825 --> 00:42:19,036
I will be disappointed,
but I have no regrets.

742
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:21,705
<i>I believe</i>

743
00:42:22,331 --> 00:42:23,666
<i>I did my best.</i>

744
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:35,928
-I feel like it's over now.
-Are you relieved?

745
00:42:36,637 --> 00:42:37,805
I don't know.

746
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:41,100
SI-HYUN, GO TO THE VOTING AREA NOW

747
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:42,309
Bye.

748
